subject: Modify SMACK manifest according three domain model and update CMakeLists.txt
commitMessage:
Modify SMACK manifest according three domain model and update CMakeLists.txt

Since SMACK only allows three labels, "_"(floor), "User", "System"
The labels of manifest are not appropriate

Solution:
- Apply default manifest (request floor label)
- Assign User label in 
   /opt/usr/apps/org.tizen.menu-screen/data
   /opt/usr/apps/org.tizen.menu-screen/data/dbspace
   /opt/usr/apps/org.tizen.menu-screen/data/shortcut
- Update CMakeLists.txt

Change-Id: I238ae2bc846bfeaee56c78b8617c391e1f004aad
Signed-off-by: seong.chung <seong.chung@samsung.com>

subject: Remove SMACK rule file(.rule) according three domain model
commitMessage:
Remove SMACK rule file(.rule) according three domain model

Since SMACK only allows three labels, "_"(floor), "User", "System"
The labels of current rule file are not appropriate

Solution:
- Remove rule file (org.tizen.menu-screen.rule)
- Remove install statement about installing rule file described in CMakeLists.txt
- Remove file path and name declaration of spec file (packaging/org.tizen.menu-screen.spec)

Reference site
https://wiki.tizen.org/wiki/Security:SmackThreeDomainModel

Change-Id: I66ec98463873acf1ce58dfabf3c239b4f4c3ba7e
Signed-off-by: seong.chung <seong.chung@samsung.com>
